author: Caitlin Oprysko and Zach Montellaro
title: Wisconsin voters brave long lines amid coronavirus crisis
description: Tuesday’s elections also come after 24 hours of disarray because of conflicting state orders and court rulings.
content:
But crowds swarmed to the polls despite the states being under a stay-at-home order by Evers a step taken to allow for social distancing in an attempt to blunt the spread of the virus that has wracked the nation.
